  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Assistance, Protection and Durable Solution Needs of Refugees at Heightened Risk in Kampala, Uganda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Refugees, Vulnerable victims of torture</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to achieve its objectives by providing short term therapy and mandatory home visits to enhance the evaluation of the client&#x2019;s condition and allow for better care. Local psychiatrists and medical institutions are used in emergencies to provide enhanced assistance and perspective on the client&#x2019;s condition. Where necessary, the accommodation or provision for the subsistence needs of clients may be provided. Additionally group therapy sessions may be provided for clients who have experienced similar trauma. The project also provides training for partners and refugees in identification, assistance, protection and durable solutions to teach practical skills in case identification, prioritization and best practices. Additionally sensitization &amp;amp; protection training  on how to identify, prevent and respond to potential risk situations is provided.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project has four main objectives. The first is to seek the protection of refugee survivors of torture and violence (STV) through resettlement case processing. The second objective is to improve the mental and emotional well-being of refugee STV through the provision of psychosocial services. The third objective is to improve access to basic needs for refugee STV through the provision of social services &amp;amp; external referral. The last main objective is to build the capacity of the partner organizations in the timely identification, assistance and protection of refugee STV through training.</narrative>
  </description>
